      "writtenOn": "2018-11-21T02:22:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "1. Sequence of events is: config is expanded to create VM records, then VM records are processed to create actual virtual machines (GCE instances). Record\u0027s existence suggests a GCE instance needs to exist, but not that it actually exists yet (will add fields to the record to convey whether or not the GCE instance actually exists).\n\n2. Yes, any time the config changes the records will be updated. vm.Attributes will be used at virtual machine creation time, which means although the record is updated right away, the GCE instance is not updated ever. New attributes take effect by deleting and recreating with the new attributes. This matches MP behavior with updating instance templates. Existing GCE instances are unaffected, changes take effect as leases expire.\n\nI\u0027ll add a README.md explaining this later, for now I added a very brief explanation to the model package.",
      "parentUuid": "17adeb12_1032d589",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 56,
        "startChar": 0,
